    <h2>Moving from Unit Costs to Assembly-Based Estimating</h2>
    <p>
      Modern scaling requires a shift from simple unit cost lookups to <strong>Assembly-Based Estimating</strong>. Instead of pricing a single stud or a gallon of paint, custom software allows you to build complex assemblies. A single "Interior Wall" assembly can trigger a full Quantity Takeoff (QTO) including labor, fasteners, waste factors, and specialized equipment.
    </p>

    <p>
      This approach ensures that nothing is missed. It moves the expertise from the individual estimator's head into the company's digital infrastructure. This mitigates "key-man risk," where the departure of a senior estimator could paralyze the sales pipeline.
    </p>

